The input files in this directory are used for verifying that mode_box 
and non mode_box switches of the code are equivalent.

The two cases without the arakawa scheme given identical results
The two cases with the arakawa scheme give identical results

The difference between the arakawa scheme and normal scheme is miniscule, and both results change the same with dissipation (issue 26)

These tests were satisfied for r2838.

(checked previously that this also holds when signB/signJ = -1, in issue 43)

